3.3 Multi-Theme WorkspaceThis is the core Shopify-inspired workflow that separates HamroTourist from generic website builders:FeatureBehaviorPublished ThemeThe single live theme serving real visitors. Only one can be published at a time per tenant. Changing the published theme triggers an atomic swap with zero downtime.Draft ThemesAny number of inactive theme instances. Agencies can fully customize a draft without affecting the live site. Perfect for seasonal campaigns, redesigns, or experimenting.Theme InstancesEach theme instance is a full copy of a base theme plus all customizations: section order, content, colors, fonts, media. Stored as structured JSON in PostgreSQL.Snapshot / Version HistoryEvery publish action saves a versioned snapshot. Agencies can roll back to any previous version with one click. Snapshots are stored per tenant per theme.Preview ModeDraft themes can be previewed via a secret-token URL: ?preview_token=<uuid>. Share with clients before going live. Token expires in 7 days.Theme DuplicationAny theme instance can be duplicated. Useful for creating a seasonal variant from the current live theme without starting from scratch.Key RuleOne PUBLISHED theme per tenant at all times. All others remain DRAFT. Publishing a new theme atomically unpublishes the previous one. A full snapshot is saved before every publish to enable instant rollback.4. Database Schema Design4.1 Core Website Builder TablesTable: website_themesStores all theme instances (both published and drafts) per tenant.SQLCREATE TABLE website_themes (
